\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid12023959 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Can you tell me your full name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Now or - Rose Jeanette Underwood.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 And your address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 17 Rectory Road, Dagenham.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 And you're a widow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Can you remember your year of marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 I think it was 19 - I don't know why I keep - the end of 1922 - I don't think it was - me boy's got me marria
ge lines, see I give everything to him, policies and everything if anything happened to me. Yes, it may have been there - I know wasn't four years after the war though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Was it before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No. No. 1918-1919 - well might have been 1922 - look, wait a minute, I've been }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8132483 Married}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974  - can't remember that now. Nearly fifty years. Anyway say 1922, I think that would be right enough, if it's anything else - well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 How old were you when you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8132483 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Twenty-two, you see, I was rather young getting }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8132483 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Can you tell me the year of your birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes, 1897.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 And where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Priory Street, Bow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 How many years did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Ho, now you're asking now. I couldn't tell you because we lived in so many places.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Were you there a long time do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 It was all round Bow - Bromly-by-Bow where we lived. I was born in Priory Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Can you remember the house at Priory Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 So you were very tiny when you left there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Yes, I don't remember - I remember living in Oxes Street - that's still Bromley but no, Bromley - you know, Bromley-by-Bow, you don't hear it mentioned now, it's called Poplar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 You lived in lots of houses round there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Round there - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 What was the first house that you can remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Still in Bow. Oxes Street, I think, that's Bromley-by-Bow. That's round about that way, you see, it's all round about that way. I remember living in Franklin Street and I was only young 
then. And then we lived in - I say we lived in Oxes Street, then we lived in Gray Street, still Bow.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Where did you live when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh, now you've asked - still in Bromley because I went to a school called the Red school - th
at was in Bromley. And from there I think I went to Old Palace school. That's still in Bow, that's opposite Priory Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Is that when you were eleven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh no. No. I was - when I was eleven I was living - that's when the separation was and - I w
ere living - we were living different places. I remember Bow Common Lane that - at that time, see. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 So you had ever such a lot of moves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Moves. Moving all the time. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 But mainly in Bromley?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh, always in Bromley - Bromley-by-Bow - all around there. Grace Street we lived in - Stratfield Road. All in Bromley-by - all round.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Have you any idea how many moves you made roughly or is too many?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No, I know it doesn't matter but - we - then you see it doesn't seem possible tha
t you could keep being around, you see, even in - from - Gray Street was the last one - we made a move to - I should think it was what then - over that - that way 'cos that was over the waterway, what I call - we went round the short, well, I don't suppos
e you know where that is but that's still Bromly-by-bow. Lead - must lead you into West Ham or Plaistow - I think that's where we went to live, there. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Why did you make these moves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Now you're asking me. See.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Was it anything to do with your father's job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
No, because he was a - he had a good - well, he did have a good job - he was boiler maker but he mostly was a round of fish and winkles and shrimps, see, all that but he was a - but I think myself why the moves was on it might have
 been debts, see what I mean. And different things they all seemed to come - come and go. I should think it may have been debts or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 To avoid people catching up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Catching up, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 You didn't move to bigger or better houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh never - never better - never better.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Three brothers, no sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Could you tell me the order that you came in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Well, yes, I was the eldest - my brother Sonny he was next, I think
 there was two years in between, then there was Eddie, Eddie Finch - he lives at East Ham. John he lived at Farnborough, Hampshire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 How many years were there between Eddie and Sonny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 I should think about the same. Yes, two - two and a half years.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 And between the last }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8613746\charrsid8921974 tw}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 o?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Eddie and - and Johnnie. Well, Johnnie is sixty-five this year. I think there might have been a longer space there - don't know if any children come and we lost them or something in between, I don't know. No. But I k
now after - John, after Johnnie when my mother was with this other man, I know she had a child by him but that died, I know that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 You don't know if any of your mother and father's children died while you were a little girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 As far as I know, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 How old was your father when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Couldn't tell you that. Me mother was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 How old was he when he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 I should think there was only about a year in between them. I don't know the death of me father and I don't know if 
he's alive or dead now but he can't be alive. That's how things were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 There was about a year's difference between him and your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Him and me mother, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 He was older by about a year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes. Might have been, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 He's from - still around Bow and Bromley. They both lived around there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Was he born round there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 As far as I know. See.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 His job was boiler maker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Well he was a boiler maker - he had a lovely job but he - he never
 did it - he liked being out open air job, you know, fishing - shrimps and winkles. He used to go all the way up to London to the markets and get all his stuff and sell it all before he got home - he had all his customers because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Where would he go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
He didn't go fishing - he went to the market - that would be - Billingsgate - would be Billingsgate market. And I walked up there with him with his barrow, all the way there and he sold his stuff coming back and I used to have to go to mind the barrow.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did he do this instead of being a boiler maker or as well as?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh no, he - when he was on - doing this shrimps and winkles he never went to work at all - only did that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 You can remember him going to work as a boiler maker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Boilermaker, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 And also working on the fish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Fish. Yes. But he didn't do the two jobs together. No, I think perhaps work fell off a bit or something in those days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Do you know which he preferred?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh he wanted - he liked the open air 'cos he could get about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did he do any other jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Not as I know - yes, a - a bookie. Or tried to be a bookmaker but he always lost - he never - he never got away with anything. And I think that's why half our moving troubles were through that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 This is when you were a little girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Little, yes. I don't know if - I know one - sometimes he'd come home and he'd take us out - buy me a lovely dress and all these things and everything and the next day perhaps it have to all be sold, se
e. Money. He - he was all right but as I say - he was a gambler - a bad gambler and I think that was the - a lot of the trouble-gambling was most of our trouble. That's why I hate these laws now - they're making gambling legal - I do really. I've feels as
 though sometimes when I goes up to those shops I could smash those windows. That's how it gets me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Because of what you remember about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 When we was children - yes. And it is the truth - and I know it's the truth in lots of families. My brother
s would have been the same but they got wise. That it was one thing or the other and it did them good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did he do anything else that you can remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No.. No. He was a - good clean minded man I do know that. I don't think he ever done anything wrong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 When did you lose contact with him, how old were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Well, when I lost contact with him this last time was - during this war - last war. and I mean he used to like his own money you know and that and my husband got to know him and he didn
't think he could - he should impose on me and he came - after the war and he thought that we were going to let him live with us. But I couldn't because I had me mother. You see, with all of it -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 You had your mother living with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 And they were separated?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Yes. When she got bombed out in London - I went and brought her home to me - her and - because in between those times they did marry, her and this - Mr Brown, I always call him Tom, never called him anything else. She - I 
had to bring her back because she was - come from - In Limehouse in a shelter and if you'd have seen the people there - her friend was killed down there and they were all in this shelter. Well I went down to her - when - I come home from work one morning 
a
nd brought her back with me, see, to live with us. Well - couldn't do it - well I - didn't like it and not only that I was working for Civil Defence, you know, in the A.R.P.'s and - I was helping other people so I should help me own shouldn't I and - see,
 
I - I worked with St Georges hospital, Five Elms. I was at the first aid, A.R.P. gas and you know I have - I've got all me certificates for that. Helped her. Well when I went down and saw her - thir - all their houses were in - they was all down this shel
ter. So of course after that she always lived with me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 So you couldn't have your father really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 He went away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes. Well my husband told him to go. Well he went and he stayed that night he went - he used to stay in a - wasn't a 
lodging house - you know St Andrews hospital do you know St Andrews hospital - well you see it on a train as you go by. Yes. Well it was like - well, years ago it was called the workhouse. You know. Yes. Well, he went and stayed there that night because w
e
 told him to go and that night that place got bombed out. And wherever he went after that, I know I - he was alive and nothing happened to him - I know he was all right. They transferred them all to London or somewhere or in some place and I never heard f
rom him again. I don't know what became of him at all and as I say I wouldn't get in contact because of me mum, see, well - well, I think it was difficult - all my life's been difficult. All my life.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Can you remember being in financial difficulties - can you remember your father being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Always - oh yes, yes. Well he always had his shrimps and winkles and all that but you see I didn't live with him did I, see, I didn't live with him after I went back to me mother and - you don't know, see. I know he had to keep the boys in the home
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 But up to the time you were eight you were living with your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 And during that time your father did mainly the winkle and shrimpt business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Was he always in work up to that time that you can remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Well, as far as I can remember used to go - used to go every day and come home we used to - wasn't all - we never had the best of food or the best of anything those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 How old was your mother when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh - she wasn't very old - well I don't know - forget now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Can you remember when she died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 My mother? Well I could get - I think she died - she's been dead - I think she died in February - she's been dead - well, my hus
band died a year afterwards - thirteen months afterwards - so when he - he died in '61 so she must have died in - '59 or '60. yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 And how old was she then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Eighty-five. Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Had she any - jobs before she got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8132483 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh I think she - in service or something like that. Yes, in service. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did she work after she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8132483 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974  to your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Well as far as I know she didn't. Not those - because I remember her - as being there
 with her with the chil - the others - the children. I don't think she worked then. But she did - before she left us - she worked 'cos she - was a waitress and she worked up New Road somethere like that - Commercial Road round that way. And - I suppose wh
o
ever this fellow was she must have picked up with because - she came home late one night and I remember this - that was in Oxes Street, Bromly-by-Bow, I don't know how old I was - six or seven - and - 'course father and her tackled he - I think it comes u
p
 to a punch up and I remember her picking a lamp up - a para - 'cos we had paraffin lamps then, we never had gas - paraffin lamp up and I saw my father out it with his hands like that, crush it right out. Well then after that - a matchbox come through the
 
window. Whoever it was that brought her home - of course my father went down there and he went after him and they had - they had a punch up. That's as far a - I never saw any of it - I know what happened but - and then after that it went on for a little w
hile and then - she went away and she sent a card home saying that - they was at Southend, she was having a nice time and she wasn't coming home anymore. I can see my father sitting crying in the chair.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 And you were only were only a little girl about eight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Yes, yes, I had three brothers. My youngest brother, Johnnie, was ill with measles and I had those other two and she went away and left us with the lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 How old was Johnnie then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Johnnie was only about nine months old or something like that. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 She was working as a waitress you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 In the evenings or all day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 All day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Who looked after you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Well we did, nobody else lived -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did she have any other job that you can remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No. No
. Only this here - she used to go out every day. We didn't know what she was doing of. I didn't know. Dad never - she - I never remember seeing much of her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 She worked full hours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes, all day. Well, waitresses worked eight 'til eight at night. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
When she moved in with this Tom Brown, she left home when you were eight, she moved in with Tom Brown and how old were you when - you first went to live with her again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh - I should think within a year - within a year of her leaving 'cos you see, my father moved up there see to get in touch with -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 To Southend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
No - she only went to Southend for holidays. No, when I lived with dad he took us all up to this place in New - in Commercial Road, I remember it, a watch shop with we live
d - had a room upstairs. Well if - from there where we all got pushed around - separated, you see, and - she went to live - she wasn't living in that place there, she went to live in another place too. And I went - that's when I went to live with her but 
we only had one room. I could have been - stayed at me father's place. Well in between that time they'd been put into a home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 The boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes. But he kept them for a good while I should think but I mean when you're young like that at that age - you
 only remember wrongs - the unhappy things, you don't remember any - well I don't think there was any good - not to say good times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 You were about nine then when you rejoined your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 I reckon so, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Do you think you stayed with her most of the time until you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh I stayed with her all the time then, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did she go out to work then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh yes, she'd always go out to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 What did she do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Well, we worked at the same place. We worked at the Rope Gro
und - we worked - what was the name Ecko Battery in Bow Comm on Lane - I know she worked there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 She worked in various factories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Factories, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 And she had one more child who died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes. She had another child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Do you know how old you were when that happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Couldn't have been very old - couldn't have been - everything seems to - I was still going to school anyway - still going to school.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 But she didn't have any other children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No, no, no. Was only us four an
d my brother - Sonny - he died. He was only fifty-eight - fifty-five when he died. It's all - it's all through neglect - he might not have been ill like he was only for that. He was a lovely boy. He was a drummer boy in the Army - the first world war and 
'cos he was a stretcher bearer on the field 'cos they took them then at that age. But - but - as I say, I remember - I remember the day the war broke out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 When you were living with your mother and Mr Brown did you look after yourself when you came home fro - school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Your mother was at work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 She was at work. There was no - never anything much there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 You just fended for yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Which house can you remember most that you lived in? Can you remember a home
 when you were living with your mother and father and three brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Well - Oxes Road, yes, I remember that but I don't remember us being a family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Can you remember the actual - house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Well we only had one room in the house - or an upstai
rs part we lived - people lived downstairs I know that. And there was the first Christmas there and we had a Christmas tree. I don't know - I think it was downstairs Christmas treet and I think I used to go and pinch the sweets out the bag and eat them.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Not very old, but I remember it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 About six?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No, must have been older - oh, wait a minute, it was before, yes, about six I should think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 And you think you had the upstairs of the house.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes, was the upstairs, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Just one room or more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 I don't know if it's one room or more, I couldn't tell you that for - for a fact.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Can you remember if there was a kitchen separate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Don't remember going into a kitchen. That might have only been one room 'cos years ago everyboy had one room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Can you remember where you slept in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No, I can't. I suppose we had a couple of beds in - must have had a couple of beds in the room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 What about as you got older - can you remember any of the houses you lived in with your mother and Mr Brown?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Well we never lived in houses, they was all - oh well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Or Rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Well we lived in - I don't - it wasn't a - wasn't a home life really. We was in there and had our meals and - ne
ver a - never had friends come into see - never brought friends in or anything - you couldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 It was usually one room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 One room, yes. You was either in or out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 You lived in that room all of you and slept in the room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes. Sometimes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did you occasionally have separate rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Well - when we - before I was - well, I was getting older then and I used to make my bed up when mother had - we did have a kitchen room then - well, a - a little room and - of a night time I used t
o make my bed up in a - kitchen to sleep. Mother slept in the other room, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 So you had your own separate bed then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Bed then - yes. Oh, I never slept in with them any time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 So you must have had some little room where you could go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Some - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 And your brothers were in the childrens home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 My brothers was away then in the home - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did your father ever pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Was the washing done at home or was it sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 It was done at home as far as I know. I come home from work and done it on me own - me own washing myself as well yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did your mother make the family's clothes? Did she make clothes for you and herself
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Well, now, remember having machine that she mu
st have made something sometime or other or perhaps made machinging to go out, I couldn't tell you. But she did have a machine. So she must have done something.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 You can't remember her making anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2070\langfe1033\langnp2070\insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2070\langfe1033\langnp2070\insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did she mend clothes for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh I think she - I think while she was there she kept us tidy and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Were your clothes usually new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8613746\charrsid8921974 Oh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 , more or less secondhand. Somebody elses's. yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Where were your clothes bought or obtained - do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Well you know, years ago they used to have these stalls do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Stalls at church halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Secondhand - oh no, I don't think church halls - secondhand stalls, you know, used to have stalls with clothes - jumble sales or something like that I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 When did you get new clothes - at any special time or just when you needed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Not any special time. We never had a - a rig out, you know, we never had that - some children - I'd have a new pinafore sometimes now and again but - I do remember my - me mother making me a velvet dress once. Now come to think of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 But you didn't have a rig out for Christmas or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2070\langfe1033\langnp2070\insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2070\langfe1033\langnp2070\insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 -Oh no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 But you had clothes when you needed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did your mother or father make shoes or mend them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No, they never - no, I don't think he made 'em no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did he mend them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did Mr Brown?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh he never done anything - no. He wouldn't do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Were your boots usually new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Secondhand sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 And you would get those from the same place as the clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Well, wherever they - wherever they come from. If they fit they fit you see. I can't recall anything like that. Mother - my mother, as I say, she was 
never indoors. Never indoors - she was always out. Except sleeping and meal times - or she'd sit and read a book sometimes. She liked a book.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did your father or Mr Brown help your mother with any of the jobs in the house - cleaning up the room or cooking - washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 I don't - I don't think so. I think he would have done if - they were left there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Your father?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 no, Tom Brown. I don't remember me mother and father being all that together much you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 You don't remember Mr Brown doing much about the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No, he didn't - no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did they ever redecorate the rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did your father ever look after you - dress you or undress you or put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 I don't remember but I know we've all slept togethe
r in a big bed when we were younger but - no, I don't remember - he - my father - he didn't think it was right - he always had - you see - girl should be with a woman - that was his idea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did Mr Brown have any personal relationship with you - was he like a father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
No. Disgusting - as far as - what I think - I didn't know - I hated him you see and anything what - if he did anything good it wouldn't be good in my sight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 So you had as little to do with him as you could?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 So he never read stories to you or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh no. No. No, we never had anybody read to us - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did your father ever take you out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Where did he take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Only for a walk - that's all - around, you - know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 And you used to go with him and watch his barrow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did he ever look}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8613746\charrsid8921974 ed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974  after you when your mother was out - see you had your meals and put you to bed or see that you went to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 I don't know - I don't r
emember - I can't recall 'em - can't recall them at all doing anything. I might - but - he - no, he - he thought a lot of us in his way, he - he'd have been all right if he'd have had the right woman but - he didn't have.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 What job did Mr Brown do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Well he was another one - later on in life he worked in the docks - in the docks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did you have any special jobs that you had to do about the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Well, if it was there to do I'd do it, you see. I mean she - of a morning she'd go to work, we
ll it was left anyhow, well, there was tidying up - do - light the fire or do something like that. But he - times that he'd be - my mother was out to work he'd do the housework, see, he was that - so she had to keep him, she had to work to keep him, that'
s the sort of man she got in with. See that's another why I used to detest him. I think it\rquote 
s a film the other night with the poor dear little kiddies - they were thieving to feed themselves - you didn't see it did you? It wasn't yesterday, it was one evening in the week and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Softly, Softly or Z Cars?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Yes, it was - yes, it was in something like that. Well you see now look at her - well, I'm - I can't be wicket but I - I could class my mother like that. Sometimes not always - not always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 I remember that vividly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes, poor little dears weren't they? They were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 So you think your life was a little bit like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Like that - yes. Not as bad - but - she wouldnot let us steal for anything but of course then she didn't know they were stealing did she?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 But you weren't told when you come home you do this and you do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No. No. Was just there - she'd leave it it'd be done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did you look after your brothers a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Well, I did when - I did when we were first left, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 You helped dress them and fed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Yes. Fed them. All I could cook was rice and I know - I cooked rice and we used to have that. That was easy for me to cook. I don't remember cooking anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did they do anything to help you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Well they were too young weren't they really. I mean the - Johnnie was ill with measles. Then later on when he got better I know me other brother had measles and I remember me dad buying him some grapes. And I got a good hiding for eating some. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Well - now I remember when me mother was with us we was always put to bed early - six - half past six and we used to see the children playing outside. Yes, that's - that was years before that wasn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Do you remember why you were put to bed early - did they think you wanted a lot of sleep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes, I think it was for care. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did your mother put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Do you know what age you started putting yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Oh don't know - just say, gon on, up to bed you and up you go. That was years before that now, that's come back to me - that's in Stewarts cottages, still Bromley-by-Bow. Little place where we lived - nice little place there. She was at home then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did you share a room with your brothers when you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 I should think I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Would you have slept with them in the same bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 I don't know. I don't think so. I don't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 But generally speaking you didn't sleep with your parents.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 I don't think so - oh no, never, never, ever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Never had baths then. We'd have to be - down in the kitchen in front of the fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 You had a bowl or a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 A bath - yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 How often did you have a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Well I suppose - I suppose once a week as far as I know, still I can't call to mind - but me mother was - while she was at home we'd have to be clean I know that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 When did you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Well I think she was pretty good with that too as far as I - I suppose when you bathed you had clean clothes on, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Where did you have your meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh now you're asking. Suppose we'd have them in the living room or somewhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 If you had a separate kitchen would you have had your meals there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Well I don't remember that - I don't think so. Had it in - well, if we had a kitchen and we had the table well then we'd have our food off that table. I can't recall - I can't call - getting a meal -
 you know what I mean, those things - things don't stick in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Everything was generally a bit disorganised?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 What did she generally cook on or what did you cook on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh, I cooked on the fire 'cos we used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 A range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 A range, yes. Yes. You'd have hobs wouldn't you, on the sides.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 When was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Well - what I'm call - calling to my mind now is not then when we was at home - I was at home with mum but not the boys - my mother was out to work before I got
 up in the morning and I suppose I'd make myself a cup of tea a bit of bread and butter and go to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 You had it on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 On me own, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 What about at lunch times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Well I think she leave me then - when she was at work in those days I remember being left with tuppence to get what I liked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 And in the evening - would you get your own in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Well I daresay perhaps we'd have a meal when we came home. Those sort of things I never -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Can you remember what sort of things you ate - you said you cooked rice for your brothers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Cooked rice for me brothers and that but I - I
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 You'd have bread and butter for breakfast - what might you buy with your tuppence?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Well - tell you the truth I used to buy oranges - I liked oranges.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 What sort of things would you have in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
I can't - I can't even remember that but - 'cos as I say, she didn't come home from work 'til late. I can't recall it - can't bring that back at all. But I suppose we'd h
ave bread and jam or something like that - we'd have something. We wouldn't be without.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did your mother ever bake that you can think of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Well, later on as I get older - as I'm getting older 'cos you're - I'm still in the child period. Yes, well 
then I don't remember her - I suppose she did. She must have done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did most people bake their bread then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes. Oh not bread no, she wouldn't bake bread or anything like that. No, on no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 She wouldn't make jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No, I don't think she was that kind of a person.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 But you could buy jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh you could buy jam - and bread and everything then, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 She didn't bottle fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2070\langfe1033\langnp2070\insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2070\langfe1033\langnp2070\insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Or make pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Make wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Make any medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Licquorice powder. Licquorice powder. I had plenty of that - I know she used to give us that - if we weren't well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did she buy that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 The powder and mix it, you know, put it in your tea so as you wouldn't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did she ever brew any beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 You didn't have a garden did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Don't remember a garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did your father ever have an allotment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Not my father, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Can you remember how many times a week you ate meat?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No, I couldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Can you ever remember eating tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Oh no, not tinned meat. Unless it - if we bought corned beef but - never bought - never had tins of anything, no. I daresay she buy some - leg of lamb and stew that and - I suppose she'd had our - her littl
e bit of joint - and - well, me grandmother used to and so she must have - followed suit I should think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Do you think you ate meat as much then as you would now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh you, I think you ate meat - plenty of meat - you could get plenty of meat anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 But you're not sure you had it all that often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Well - I suppose if she cooked a dinner we'd have meat. But I say - I don't - can't recall - I can't recall a meal that - sitting down all together at the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did you ever get extra meat such as rabbit from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Oh no. Not poaching - you could buy a rabbit for sixpence. Buy a - sixpence - they used to come round with them on a barrow, see, lovely rabbits.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 You don't think they got them from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh, well, I couldn'
t tell you it was - they could easily have been locked up if they'd have been caught but - I know they used to come round with them and lovely fresh herrings. They used to come round - what was it - sixteen for fourpence. Fresh herrings - they were lovely
 then. Well of course a fresh herring - if we had a fresh herrings as good as all the meat in the world.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did your father or Mr Brown have more to eat than the women in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No. Well, I don't - I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Were you allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh yes, I don't think - we never had any restrictions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Could you eat what you wanted or did you have to eat everything that you were given?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 I don't - mother wasn't very strict on that. I suppose if we were hungry we would eat it. See, that's about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 But you wouldn't be expected to eat everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2070\langfe1033\langnp2070\insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2070\langfe1033\langnp2070\insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No, no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 I should think - yes, I should think so if it was there, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 If you wanted something like the salt could you ask for it or would you have to wait until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh no, we could reach and take it - I think if it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way and sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 They weren't strict on that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No. You could relax, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Could you bring toys or a book to the table?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Oh I don't believe - I don't remember having any. See. So - not - not to the table. I don't remember seeing the - the children - the boys with any toys. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Could you leave the table when you wanted or did you have to wait?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 I think we could have - left if we'd wanted to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 If you'd had your meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 You can't remember the whole family sitting down together for a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Can you remember your mother serving you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 I should think it was all - if we had it it was served up on a plate and given to us all the lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Would your father be served first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 I don't think so - I don't think there was any - naturally but - I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Who fed your younger brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
My brothers - nobody there to feed them only me was there unless as I say, she was out to work even when these children were young so - I suppose I did, yes. Oh, I remember
 when my brother was ill, Eddie, when he was ill and I got into trouble for eating his grapes - I never ate them all, had one or two 'cos he didn't want them well - and - me dad was worried - he used to have to go out and do his bit of what went to market
 and do these things and - suppose he said, she ate my grapes and - that's about it. So - well I - I must have gone in and done things for him when he wasn't well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 You were quite a competant little girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 I had to be didn't I? Those things and - you don't want any teaching to do those things - they come to you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did you have a good relationship with your mother before she left home - - could you talk to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 I don't remember - I don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 What about after, when you went to live with her again, did you get on quite well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Well she still went out to work all day and I went to work - we worked together in the same factory.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did you get on well with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh yes. See, see that everything was all right for - mind you my
 mother in these late - in her later years she'd have given me the world. Too late.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 You can't remember feeling close to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Not close enough to her, no. If she was ill and all that I'd - we'd be together and you know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did she ever show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No. I don't ever remember - kissing me and - until later years when she used to go home when I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8132483 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 . As I say, those times years ago she was - I was romantic you see. She read books, she read novels and they're no good to you 'cos the
y fill your head up with ideas and she thought she'd get someone - a better man. If she'd have got herself a better man good luck to her, but she didn't - that's - that's all all I agree with.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 You said she was romantic - she wanted things to be nice and happy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
She used to look beautiful you know, when she was dressed. She did. Only the other day I saw, these old pictures, couple of Noel Cowards pictures I saw and I could see my mother in these lovely dresses and high hats, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did you feel happy about her when you were little - having a pretty mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No, no, not then - now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 If you had any worries could you tell her when you were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No, no, no. I don't think so. No. I remember once when I had a - first period I'd ever h
ad and - I said something to her about it. Oh, she said, that's nothing. See, that's all I got to know. You learn more in the factory that what you do outside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 So you didn't have much of a relationship with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No, not much of a relationship.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did you with your father before you lost contact with him - do you think you were closer to your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Well I used to - when he was in his lodgings - but I'll - tell you what. It looks as though me mum's been wrong all the time what I've been t
elling you, but I do remember her - she must have tried to make a go of it because she - I told you she had a machine, well I remember her making little dresses and hanging them up in the shop to try and sell so she must have tried to make a go of it with
 the old man and couldn't I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 She did make dresses then and she did sew?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes she did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 You remember the velvet one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 That's right - the velvet - made for you - for me, yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 You haven't given the impression that she was all bad - you said she was very romantic?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes, that's right. And she must - she couldn't have been with my father all that time could she, from when they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8132483 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974  and that, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Well I don't think - I don't think they bothered much about that. I don't think they bothered much about that but then because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Were they ambitious for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh, I don't know about me - no, she wasn't ambiotious my mo
ther wasn't - then - so as long as - if I went to work I brought in some money. I remember - going - in the laundry you know to learn the trade. Well that wasn't a lot of money then so it was only about six shillings a week, well I'd already got this job 
at the rope ground being in eight and something a week so I had to leave that place and come and go back to me job again see? Yes, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Do you think that she hoped you would have a better life than she had had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No, I don't think she bothered about that - I don't think she bothered much about that any rate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 You weren't aware of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2070\langfe1033\langnp2070\insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2070\langfe1033\langnp2070\insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2070\langfe1033\langnp2070\insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did they want you to behave in any special way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did they have any principles that you know of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No, I don't think so. We ha
d to sit down - for them - but I don't remember being with the family to sit round a lot, you see, so I can't say about table manners or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did they ever tell you to do certain things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh, I had to do lots of things - I could do a lot of chores, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 What about behavious - do you remember being told off for doing certain sorts of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Or were you expected to be a nice sister to your younger brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 I know - I don't think they bothered much about tha
t, no, I don't think - well I wasn't with me brothers to be - after him - they went in the home see, my brothers Johnnie - how old was he - he was only a little lad in a sailor suit about three years old when he was in the ho-e and there was three of them
 in the home so I can't say that any - well, remem - like things like now, my brothers didn't really know much about me until we got to meet after - see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 You were almost an only child for most of your childhood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did they have any views about swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Oh no, I don't - well, I don't think we swore - I don't think, you know, that - well to me it was vile so I don't suppose they - I know that she's had arguments with the man she was living with but - he could swear but - it never affected me in that like.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 What would have happened if she'd ever caught you doing anything wrong - can you remember any incident at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes - well actually like - I suppose I was a girl who liked boys, you see, and it - this was during the fir
st call up of the war and the Territorials were around and I knew she - somebody had told her I was round the school where the boys were - I knew she come round and told me they're not the sort of things you should to - it will lead to wrong things and tr
ouble and not only that I remember her words were 'you don't know what you do to those boys.' So she was - I know now but - we didn't bother much then did we, it was all fun.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 But she came and said that to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 This was when you were about sixteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh, about sixteen, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 When you were a little girl can you remember ever being punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 You didn't ever get a good hiding for anything at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No, no. Not as I know - not as I remember unless she spent
 a shilling that belonged to me and I didn't like that. That made me cross, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did you tell her you were cross or couldn't you dare to say anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh yes. Oh yes, I could talk to her and all that - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Some times we get the impression
 that parents were strict and the children couldn't tell them things that they had done - that you were afraid of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh - well, I don't think so. You see, as I say, my mother was full of pl-asure and she'd go out and leave me all day long, that wo
uldn't matter, but she wouldn't - I don't think she'd - if I did do anything wrong I don't think she would have - given me a hiding or anything like that - oh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 You remember that play on television you told me about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 That little girl got hit because she wasn't looking after her little brother properly
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Girl. Brother - yes. No, no, I never - no, what I meant by that was - this - the woman with the man - letting them do - make the kids like they were, see, which I - I thought was wron
g. They could have been better children if the parents had been better. And it's the same with me, I daresay I - I'd be better if I'd have - they'd have bothered about me education or anything. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 So the comparison you were making was that the children were left to go their own way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 That's right yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 And the parents didn't have a lot to do with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did people ever come in to see your parents or see your mother - did neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Not - not that - oh well we lived -
 'course those times we all - we lived in a house each person had one room wouldn't they - would live. They were friendly - friendly places.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 If your friends popped into your mother's room and had a chat with her, were you allowed to join in the conversation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 I don't think she ever - ever had many people come in - 'cos she was never in to have the people you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Where would you say you got your ideas about how to behave from - you've got very definite ideas about what people should and shoul
dn't do haven't you? Do you think you got this from your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh no, I don't think so. My grandfather was a very strict man and 'course I used to go and live with him now and again, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 For holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh no, just now and again when thi
ngs went wrong at home, I was - I had - I - they didn't want me or something or me mother - fall out with the man and clear off and - see, well, I'd go to me grandmothers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 How often did this happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh - a lot - I lived with my grandmother for about ten months once.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Now you're asking me again. So many things happened. I should say between - I might have been eleven or twelve. Might have been that.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 What were your grandparents like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh my grandmother - I loved her. Any - anything that went wrong I always went there. See.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did you regard her almost as a mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Well - I don't know as - if I classed her as a mother or an angel. See. But she - she's the one that fostered me, you know what I mean, 
when I was there I could sit down on the floor and put me head up against her legs and that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Which you couldn't do with your own mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No time - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Where did she live?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 My grandmother? Well she lived in Bromley-by-Bow, she l
ived in Gurley Street, that's when I went to live with them. And she lived in lots of - as I say they'd be in - they moved around you know, you could always get houses then, she lived in Denham Road, Bow and - Gurley - I said Gurley Street and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 That was your mother's mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 How many children did she have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Who - my grandmother? Let me see - Aunt Ginny, me mother, Uncle Jack, Uncle Fred - Wally, Johnnie and Nell, how many's that? About six.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Were some of them living at home still?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh yes, they were still at home - yes, they were still at home, yes. Where - I've got the old Bible in here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did your aunts and uncles spoil you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Well - I played with - yes, I played with my - Wally Mason, he died very young. He 
he was my uncle - he was ten days younger than I, see and - I used to play with him out in the street and that, he used to play cricket - we used to go round playing knocking down Ginger, you know. Knocking at the doors and running away. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did your grandmother go out to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh no, she - could - no, because she had such - the family didn't she, she couldn't go out to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did you have regular meals there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 When I was there, yes. And - cooked - cooked -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Somebody cooked your meals and looked after you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did you ever want to stay there permanently instead of going back to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 At grandma's. Oh yes. But as I say, grandfather he - there again there was a bit of a quarrel between grandma and grandfather a
nd - I knew - she went out - I knew where she was - she was over at my mother's and I said I didn't know, see. And he knew I knew and - he said well you go with her. So - I got turned out of there. But it was only spitefulness really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Was he strict?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
He was strict - he was religious. Religious while he was out, you know. He loved the kids. The kids used to run along - hold his hand. Thought Mr Mason was a lovely man yet inside he was different. Though he was good to his own children - oh yes, he d
id everything for them. I mean, they all - was taught violin. Aunt Nell she had to learn the - we had a organ and - and Aunt Rose, she played the organ. On Sunday evenings it used to be lovely. When they all come home from chapel we'd all - they'd all be 
in the front room and singing hymns and harmonising - it used to be lovely. So he wasn't so bad.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 What was his job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 He worked at Nicholsons the gin place. Down Short Wall, you know, West Ham it is really. You know, Nicholsons gin place - I don't 
know if it's still going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 But what did he actually do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Ooh, he was a mechanic. If anything went wrong in the factory of a night or any time, they'd come for him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Were your grandparents a little better off than your own parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh yes
, yes, well - he would be better off. He'd make himself and his holiday money he used to have an allotment and - all the stuff what he sold he put that by for his holiday. But he wouldn't have took me grandmother or the children - I don't remember them go
ing on holiday - he used to go on his own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 You could chat to your grandmother - could you tell her your own personal little worries?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh yes, yes, I think so. I think I used to tell her - you know - if anything was wrong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 What sort of things did she used to cook for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Oh - in the - with the big baked - oh, the big lovely joint in the dish and the - and when I used to go over there Sunday mornings, you know, say oh, I know what you want slice of bread dipped in the lovely gravy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did you go there every Sunday morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Well, nearly every Sunday I went over there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Even when you weren't living with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes. Well I used to go and help her 'cos she was so fat, she couldn't get down to do anything and - I used to go once
 a week and do her fireplace, even when I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8132483 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974  I still went there and we always spent Christmas with her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Don't remember birthdays. We never - even now when people send all
 the cards my - we never thought of cards or anything like that. Wasn't anything no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No presents, no cards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 You never had parties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Or anything special for tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did you know it was your birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 I don't know. Don't think so.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Do you remember anything you did with your mother and father together on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No. Because when I went to - on Christmas Day I nearly always went to me grand-mothers even as a child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 On your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did your mother not mind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Well - no, she didn't mind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 What did they do on Christmas Day - would they have had any special meat at home or a special meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Not - well, not while I was younger they wouldn't. Not as I know of. Th
ough they - she might get a few nuts or bits of fruit in or something like that - but we never had any parties or sing-songs or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Can you tell me about Christmas Day at your grandmother's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh yes, go over there in the morning and have a 
nice time and - and me dinner and me tea. Have - everything that was there same as everybody else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 What did you have for dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh, we'd have the turkey. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 And Plum Pudding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes. She used to make her own too you know. Used to h
ave a big copper - put them all in the copper there. Sit up to about twelve o'clock at night she used to cooking them all - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did she have decorations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes, I think we did used to have chains and that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Would all the other children be there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 The family - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 But not your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No. You see, at that time - me mother wasn't in with them, you see, at that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 They excluded her because she left your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes. That's right, yes. They had for the time being
 well then she gradually come round to me grandmother and then - gradually worked in with grandfather. During the wars it was, during the first world war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 She made it up again with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 What did you used to do in the afternoon on Christmas Day at your grandmothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Oh we used to have - play games. Yes, a game to - with a farthing - oh, tippit they used to call it. You had to tip up or something - turn in over - on - on a cord - something like tiddly-winks or something I should th
ink. Yes.. Used to play that. And then I - I suppose I'd go home about six or seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did you have a sing-song there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Well - no, not the kind of sing-song if we had it would've been hymns or something like that. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 The whole family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 And some of the children would play instruments or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Well, Wally - uncle Wally, Uncle John - oh and they - then they went to Canada - they - oh they came home - came over - they must have gone to Canada before the war because they 
came home as soldiers - that was Uncle - John. Well he died. And there was Fred - he went out there. And it - he went to America but when we - they were all together Sunday afternoons especially, I always remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 And this is because your grandfather was religious?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes, very - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did you have any musical instruments in your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did you learn to play anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 I learned to play meself on me grandmother's organ.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 You taught yourself did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes, yes. Used to watch them. But I can't play a note now - go wrong. But I used to play a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did you ever have to sing to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did your mother play any games with you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did your grandparents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Well - I suppose with the - Wally and those being young we all played together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 In your mother's house were there books - did they buy books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Novels. Only novels.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Your mother liked reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Reading - oh - yes. She'd buy the books and read 
'em or get them from I - borrow them or get them from - I don't know if she ever went to the library.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 What did you say they were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 The tuppeny Christian novels. They used to have Christian Novels - they used to be tuppence then they're more now a
nd - another book - I forget what the name of that is, but they were just paper - you know, tuppeny paper books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did you have magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No.. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 I suppose she had newspaper - must have done mustn't they. I don't remember but - I never read newspapers.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 You can remember your mother sitting down and reading can't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did they ever read aloud to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Or to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Do you remember a funeral in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes. Well there's me grandmother when she died. Me aunt -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 How old - oh I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8132483 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
 then. Yes, I don't remember any funerals younger, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Were you taken out visiting neighbours, friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No. And - on, 
perhaps on Saturday nights they'd go - to a friend - I don't know whoever they were, not now, but you - this girl used to sing lovely I know, we used to go there on Saturdays because me -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 You went with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes, at times - because me mother lik
ed parties you know and they - that's where they went. And of course old Tom Brown - he was a lovely singer so he was invited anywhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Were you ever taken shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Do you remember any outings at all with your parents - or with your mother - Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Not when I was young. No, no I never went out with them. I've been out on me own - used to go to Wanstead Falts - it's only tuppence on the bus then - I suppose I'd have a girlfriend with me or somebody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did you ever go away on a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
No. But - as me grandmother coming into it again - she took me to Clacton once from chapel, Virger Hall as the name of the place was, and I nearly got drowned, I fell in the water. I had to be rescued, 'cos I was - I had a fuss ma
de of me that day and me poor grandma was upset.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 That was the last time she took you to the seaside was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Well it was only - I don't think she was able to go anymore because she was - too stout and couldn't get about. I remember that. That out
ing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 That's the only time you went to the seaside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Yes, I think so. I've been to - we used to go out with the school with - somebody used to do it - the Ragged School Union, we used to go out on a brake to - went out Woodford way somewhere and w
e used to have a bun and a - lemonade I think when we got there - that was all right, we liked that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 That was at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Can you tell me how you usually spent Saturdays in those days?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Just ordinary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 You didn't do anything special?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 What about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 I went to me grandma's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 For the whole day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No, no. I'd go there perhaps and then come home to dinner, see, 'cos my dinner - our dinner wasn't ready 'til three o'clock any rate.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did you have different clothes on on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Now and again I suppose I had a nice frock or a nice pinny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 That you'd keep specially for Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes. Sometimes - well the - the pinafores, used to send them to the laundry then they used to have them al
l goffered see. I had a nice pinafore, I know I had one and I think that used to go to the laundry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 And you'd keep that for Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 And perhaps Monday to dirty it out for school and then - laundry - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Were you allowed to play games or work on Sundays or did you think that this was wrong or your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh no, they never interfered it was - no day different to any other day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 At your grandparents - what was their attitude?
