\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh, I've been - I waited outside for her, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Would she take you and tell you to wait outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 I used to go down there - round there, yes. But no, she wouldn't - 'cos at the some time
 we could go in. My grandmother's taken me in the pub and given me a pony of stout. Yes. Pony - it's a small glass - it's called a pony.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 How old were you then - do you know?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Well it must have been - under ten. 'Cos children were allowed in the 
pubs then, see. So it must - have been - I must have been young 'cos I know the children used to go in the - pubs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 They were allowed to then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes. Well my grandmother used to - when she used to go out and do her shopping then she'd just call in 
there, see. And we'd sit in there and I'd have me pony of stout, I don't know what she had but I think - she had a pony of stout.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did you like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 What - the stout? I suppose I did - I drank it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did your mother go with Mr Brown sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 When did he get home from work in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Who? Oh, when he worked - used to work in the docks - and work was hard then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 It was casual labour was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Casual labour, yes. And if that - he wouldn't go and try for anyt
hing else. If he wasn't working there well he wouldn't be working you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 So what time would he come home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Well if he was coming home I suppose about - their time about five o'clock I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did your father or Mr Brown spend evenings in during the week - would they stay at home some evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Not as I know of - he wouldn't. My father he was - always used to go out - in the evenings he used to have his fish and - oh, all round selling you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 And Mr Brown would go out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh he'd go out yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did either of them attend any clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No, not as I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did they take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Never went to sports.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 But the both were interested in the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Racing - horses, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did they go to the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Oh my father has been to the races, I don't know about Tom Brown. It's awful to call - but I've always called him that you know. Me father has been to the races.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Could you tell me how you spent Saturdays and Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 What when I was y
ounger? Well, as I say, I - play in the street or somewhere like that but - I know what I was thinking of - you asking what games or anything we played - now when I was young we used to have the barrel organs come round, you know. And we used to dance out
 
in the street, around these barrel organs, we'd do the cake walk, you know. Oh well it's cocking your legs and swinging your legs and doing this business you know and all - it was good and we used to get crowds round us watching us but of course it wasn't
 for long - about quarter of an hour 'cos he used to get collection and then go off to somewhere else.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 He did used to pass his hat round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh yes, yes. But we didn't do it for him - we did it just for ourselves - enjoy ourselves, yes. Yes. Yes, t
hat was - used to be good, and then have big skipping rope - great big thick skipping rope and go all round the turnings and picking up anybody that wanted to skip you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 You used to play out in the front of the houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes, especially Easter time - Easter holidays - Easter Monday we always used to do that, skipping round the streets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Why at Easter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 I don't know - I suppose it was a holiday - holiday Monday was all home from school or something or - and grown ups used to go round as 
well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Who did you used to play with? Were there lots of little children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Well there was children, yes, I can't think of anybody's names - not now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 But you always had someone to play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh, played with yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 You were on your own a lot of the time weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes, yes. Well I was glad to get into playing with anybody you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 I did ask you about a funeral didn't I?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes. Funerals, well - not when I was younger, only - I think I told you my mother had a little boy
 by thing me bob. Well that baby died - and there was a funeral then but I don't remember much about it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Were you particularly close to your brothers before you were separated from them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh yes, we must have been - all living together in one house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 You used to look after them a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes, I used to look after them 'cos Johnnie was only a little baby - I remember him being a baby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did you used to take him out or push him out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 I suppose I did, yes. I suppose I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 When you were living with your mother you just generally played with other children in the street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes, more or less.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Do you remember any special friend you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No, no special friend, no. You see when we lived up in Whitechapel, well, we ne
ver mixed 'cos they was all Jews up there you see - more or less, and we never mixed. Never played with those children. Well I suppose we did, we must have done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Why is this - any special reason why you didn't play with Jewish children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did they keep themselves to themselves?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
No, they didn't seem to seem to play - as far as I know. Went to school - they came to the same schools as we did. And I know when religious service was on they would go out. See, they wouldn't listen to o
ur - when it was a Christian service - when it was Old Testament they stayed in, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 But you can't remember talking to them particularly at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No, not particularly - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did they talk to the local children much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh yes. Oh, there was no quarrelling - nothing - no, nothing distasteful it's just that I don't really remember playing with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Where did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Well it would have been out in the street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did you ever have any back yard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Well there was too many people - well, backyard would be a backyard - wouldn't be a garden - that you couldn't play out in a backyard.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did you ever go into other peoples homes to play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Well I used to go in a home - a - to play - that is in London - just to play - go i
n one house and play with a - the kiddies there - that's all I can remember, I don't remember a lot of playing. I suppose I did but it - it was nothing - it wasn't interesting enough to me I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Can you tell me again what sort of games you used to play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Oh the barrel organ. Well there's - like - what they do baseball now but - we played it different. We used to have corners - four corners and a bat and ball. They used to feed you with the ball and you hit it and you run, well if you can get 
what they call a rounder - see, well sometimes you wouldn't - you'd get from corner to corner. But it you're running you get hit with the ball you're out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Is this the game that's called rounders?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Yes, it would be rounders. Yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 What else did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
As I told you, knocking down Ginger, you know, running - knocking at the door and then we used to get packets of sugar or empty packets done up as a packet - tie it up with black cotton and leave it on the ground and somebody wo
uld come and - as they went to pick it up we'd pull the string.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 You were quite mischievous?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh very, very.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 What else did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Might have done a lot of things I shouldn't say. No - yes, but still - never done - no, nothing was wrong
. Have little boy friends kissing goodnight on the corner or something like that. I forget his name now. I only knew he was - you know, used to play together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did you play mothers and father - did you have any actual toys that you played with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 N
o, not a lot - not a lot. I remember playing, when we moved - well, we lived at Plaistow I think I told you, one day, I remember playing with a little boy he - like the fruiterers was downstairs and I think we had a room up - used to play with the little 
boy and that, you know, games - digging up the garden I suppose more or less or something.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did it matter if you got dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Well if I got dirty I had to wash myself and - see, nobody - there was nobody to bother about me. If my mo
ther was at work, she never - wouldn't worry - we'd be - I'd be cleaned up, I suppose, perhaps I wasn't - perhaps I'd be dirty I don't know. But I never got - I wasn't - to get dirty or mucky you know like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Some children do and some don't don't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Do - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Could you play with anybody you wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Your mother never said, oh you mustn't play with so and so?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2070\langfe1033\langnp2070\insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2070\langfe1033\langnp2070\insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Did you belong to any youth organizations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 No, I used to - I told you the chu
rch - was more the chapel then - Sunday school and Congregational church for - the right badge you know, teetotaler. That was it - the Band of Hope, used to go there. And I - and I - we used to go to Tabernacle pictures you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Saturday morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Tabernacle. Well I have been Saturday mornings. The Tabernacle was - it was a nice little place. I think that was tuppence to go there.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Was that a religious place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Well it was - it was and it wasn't, you see. Tabernacle is religious for 
