en I - well, I was thinking of one - when I went to school, Bett Street School. Of a nighttime we used to have a - I think it was a play hour or something - we'd stay over and we used to play with magnificent toys you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 You used to stay at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Stay at school. In the evening - I don't know if we came home or whether we went back again but - we may have stayed and it was a play hour and the beautiful things that were in there. Dolls house and - big dolls - lovely.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11814545 RV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 
Well I - I'm - couldn't have been very old. I think about six, seven. You see, me age don't catch up with me 'cos I don't know because it seems as though there was ever - so much went through me during those - years while I was younger that you wo
uldn't believe all this could have happened in that time. And then we had a - they gave us tickets for a show and this was at the Pavilion, that's in - Commercial Road. Commercial Road or Milend Road - this end. And we went and saw an Aladdins play there 
and it was - well, I'd never seen anything before like that and I thought it was wonderful - the beautiful dresses and - and these people whoever it was that put it - it was all free - we had the tickets given to us so many, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12023959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13045969\charrsid8921974 Only the children went not their parents?
